先修課程或先備能力 Prerequisite Course(s):   Students taking this course need to have high motivation and considerable autonomy to learn English.      

教師聯絡資訊 Contact with Teacher
  	    You can reach me at 修齊大樓 Rm. 26530 (5F).My email is flyingvanessa@gmail.com.My office tel. number is (06)2757575#52272.       

助教資訊 Contact with Tutor


學習規範 Course Policy
1. Check Moodle Regularly:
Please check the Moodle website (http://moodle.ncku.edu.tw/) regularly. I’ll use it to post (1) Announcements, (2) Assignments and (3) Hand-Outs.
2. Reset your own Moodle email:
In order to receive important announcement from Vanessa, students MUST reset their Moodle email into primary address after the 1st class.
3. Arrive On Time:
Please arrive at class on time. Do NOT miss any classes except with a valid or strong excuse (Not valid: no handout; prepare for other courses/activities; tired… etc.). If you must miss class, please contact me about your absence BEFORE class and hand in the official document the next time.
4. Make An Appointment:
Basic etiquette: Contact me (through email, phone, or any other ways to reach me) before you abruptly show up in my office. Showing up without giving a heads-up and thinking everyone is always free for them is terribly impolite.
5. Attendance and Participation:
Students’ attendance is highly valued.
Student participation (response) is highly important as well. There are many group discussions and tasks designed for students’ participation.
Group presentation is an essential part in this course. Team work is expected.
Finishing the assigned homework (including previewing, reviewing, writing or listening tasks, discussion forum and quiz preparing, etc.) and hand in in time is each student’s responsibility.      

